cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with proof theory and the Curry-Howard isomorphism between logic and programming languages. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the computational interpretation of the proof system as session-typed processes. 
- cs.LG (Computational Logic) is another possible category as the paper deals with substructural logic and fixed points. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the suitability of the proposed algorithm as the basis for a programming language. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possibility as the paper deals with formal proof systems.
